path_aliases.markdownDescription:
A mapping that can be used to define character strings which should be substituted when resolving relative image URLs. The replacement value must be a string and supports the variables listed under https://www.sublimetext.com/docs/build_systems.html#variables.

Characters within the filename will not be substituted. The URL will still be resolved relative to the current file, unless an absolute path is explicitly given or a variable with a full path is used.

The following example allows to show image previews for a path like `~/assets/img/file.png`, which then refers to the local file at `<project folder>/app/assets/img/file.png`:

```json
{
	"path_substitutions": {
		"~": "$project_path/app"
	}
}
```
